OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: FRENCH CREEK AT PA ROUTE 345 BRIDGE
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THE STATION IS LOCATED ON THE ELVERSON PENNSYLVANIA 7.5' SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE.  THE STATION WAS INSIDE HOPEWELL FURNACE NATIONAL HISTORIC SITE (HOFU) ON FRENCH CREEK AT PENNSYLVANIA ROUTE 345 BRIDGE; RIVER MILE 21.87.  THE CREEK WAS SAMPLED AS PART OF A STUDY BY THE NPS AND PENNSYLVANIA DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION TO ASSESS NON-POINT SOURCE POLLUTION IN FRENCH CREEK AND TO DOCUMENT OVERALL WATER QUALITY IN THE BASIN.  DATA WERE PUBLISHED IN THE REPORT `AQUATIC BIOLOGY INVESTIGATION; FRENCH CREEK/CHESTER COUNTY; NPS SURVEY` (MICHAEL R. BOYER; 1993).  THE REPORT STATED; `OVERALL STREAM CONDITIONS AT STATION 1 ARE GOOD ALTHOUGH THE HQ-CWF CLASSIFICATION IS NOT BEING ATTAINED.  THE REASON  APPEARS TO BE THE PRESENCE OF HOPEWELL LAKE AND THE AGRICULTURAL LAND USE IN THE VICINITY.`  FOR MORE INFO. CONTACT HOFU'S NATURAL RESOURCES AT 2 MARK BIRD LANE; ELVERSON PA 19520.  TEL. 610-582-8773.  DATA WERE PROCESSED AND UPLOADED TO STORET BY RYAN SHY; NPS-WRD; 1201 OAK RIDGE DR.; FORT COLLINS CO 80525.  TEL. 970-225-3516.***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THE STATION IS LOCATED ON THE ELVERSON PENNSYLVANIA 7.5' SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE.  THE STATION WAS SOUTH OF HOPEWELL FURNACE NATIONAL HISTORIC SITE ON PINE CREEK AT HARMONYVILLE ROAD; RIVER MILE 21.87.  THE CREEK WAS SAMPLED AS PART OF A STUDY BY THE NPS AND THE PENNSYLVANIA DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION TO ASSESS NON-POINT SOURCE POLLUTION IN FRENCH CREEK AND TO DOCUMENT OVERALL WATER QUALITY IN THE BASIN.  DATA WERE PUBLISHED IN THE REPORT `AQUATIC BIOLOGY INVESTIGATION; FRENCH CREEK; CHESTER COUNTY; NPS SURVEY` BY MICHAEL R. BOYER (1993).  THE REPORT STATED; `FIELD CHEMISTRIES WERE TYPICAL OF A HEALTHY COLD WATER STREAM..THE PRESENCE OF WILD BROOK TROUT AND A DIVERSE AND SENSITIVE BENTHIC COMMUNITY INDICATE EXCELLENT WATER QUALITY.  SILTATION FROM AGRICULTURAL SOURCES IS PROBABLY LIMITING THE BROOK TROUT POPULATION.`  DATA WERE PROCESSED AND UPLOADED TO STORET BY RYAN SHY; NATIONAL PARK SERVICE WATER RESOURCES DIVISION; 1201 OAK RIDGE DRIVE; FORT COLLINS CO 80525 (TEL. 970-225-3516).***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: FRENCH CREEK AT COUNTY PARK ROAD (T-452)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THE STATION IS LOCATED ON THE POTTSTOWN PENNSYLVANIA 7.5' SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE.  THE STATION WAS ON FRENCH CREEK AT COUNTY PARK ROAD (T-452); RIVER MILE 17.04.  THE CREEK WAS SAMPLED AS PART OF A STUDY BY THE NPS AND PENNSYLVANIA DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION TO ASSESS NON-POINT SOURCE POLLUTION IN FRENCH CREEK AND TO DOCUMENT OVERALL WATER QUALITY IN THE BASIN.  DATA WERE PUBLISHED IN THE REPORT `AQUATIC BIOLOGY INVESTIGATION; FRENCH CREEK/CHESTER COUNTY; NPS SURVEY` BY MICHAEL R. BOYER (1993).  THE REPORT STATED; `SLIGHTLY ELEVATED LEVELS OF LEAD; ZINC; AND ALUMINUM AND BACTERIA CONCENTRATION WERE FOUND.  THE LATTER IS PROBABLY FROM AGRICULTURAL RUNOFF.  NO SOURCE OF THE METALS WAS EVIDENT..FRENCH CREEK AT STATION 4 HAS THE CHEMICAL AND BIOLOGICAL CHARACTERISTICS TO SUPPORT A HQ-CWF.  THE LIMITING FACTOR IS PROBABLY TEMPERATURE OR POSSIBLY SILTATION.`  DATA WERE PROCESSED AND UPLOADED TO STORET BY RYAN SHY; NATIONAL PARK SERVICE WATER RESOURCES DIVISION; 1201 OAK RIDGE DRIVE; FORT COLLINS CO 80525 TEL(970)-225-3516.***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM
